name: Japan 012 // 35mm film // analog photography // 2019, Japan
description:
The tori of Itsukushima, or Miyajima (宮島), which in Japanese means "Shrine Island". This gate welcomes visitors to the island near the city Hiroshima. It is a popular place for weekend activities and the island is one of Hayashi Gahō's famous "Three Views of Japan". 
This is a digital scan of an analog picture without any digital manipulation.
